play of social, cultural and physical attributes of ageing means that older people can come to have a different position in relation to time and to the self than younger people, unseating normative conventions about narrative and temporality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAgingxSocial aspectszEnglandzBarnsley (South Yorkshire). 0aOlder peoplezEnglandzBarnsley (South Yorkshire)xSocial conditions. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aageing.  aethnography.  anarrativity.  anorth of England.  aplace.  aselfhood.  asocial memory.  asubjectivity.  atemporality.1 aDegnen, Cathrine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez9783111283630oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526129888423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526129888/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPc1986d2013